# How to create workflows and actions

When you **create or edit** GitHub Actions workflows (`.github/workflows/*.yml`) or composite actions (`.github/actions/*/action.yml`), follow this guide.

## Workflow vs composite action

- **Workflow** (`.github/workflows/*.yml`): triggered by events (`push`, `pull_request`, `workflow_call`, etc.). Has `jobs` and runs on GitHub runners. Use for CI (test, build, deploy).
- **Composite action** (`.github/actions/<name>/action.yml`): reusable steps. No `on:`; has `runs: using: composite` and `steps`. Use for shared setup (e.g. Node + cache) so workflows stay DRY.

## Workflow and job names (emoji + max 4 words)

**Workflow** `name:` (top level), **job** `name:` (`jobs.<id>.name`), and **composite action** `name:` must:

- **Start with one emoji**
- Be **descriptive** and **short**: **no more than 4 words** (emoji + up to 4 words).

Examples: `🧪 Test versions`, `🟢 Node & engines`, `🛠️ Project Setup`. Avoid `test-versions` (no emoji) or long phrases.

## Workflow structure

- `name:` and job `name:` — see above (emoji + max 4 words).
- `on:` — which events trigger it (`push`, `pull_request`, `workflow_call`, etc.).
- Every **step** must have a **custom name with emoji** (below).

## Composite action structure

- `name:` and `description:` at top level (name: emoji + max 4 words).
- `runs: using: composite` and `runs.steps` (no `on:`).
- Every step must have a **custom name with emoji** (below).

## Step names (required)

Every step in a workflow or composite action must have a **descriptive custom name** that **starts with one emoji**.

- **Do not** use generic names (`Run npm ci`, `Setup Node`) or leave steps unnamed.
- **Do** prefix the name with one emoji and a short description.

### Emoji by purpose

| Purpose           | Emoji examples      |
| ----------------- | ------------------- |
| Checkout / repo   | 📥 🔽               |
| Setup / install   | ⚙️ 🛠️ 📦          |
| Test / verify     | ✅ 🧪 ✔️            |
| Build             | 🏗️ 📦              |
| Lint / format     | 📐 ✨               |
| Deploy / release  | 🚀 📤               |
| Cache             | 💾 📦               |
| Node / runtime    | 🟢 (Node)           |

### Examples

**Good:**

```yaml
- name: 📥 Checkout repository
  uses: actions/checkout@v4

- name: 🟢 Setup Node from package.json
  uses: ./.github/actions/setup

- name: ✅ Verify Node version
  run: node -v
```

**Avoid:**

```yaml
- name: Setup Node from package.json engines   # no emoji
- uses: actions/checkout@v4                     # no name
- name: Run npm ci                              # generic, no emoji
```
